Name: Alysaar Explorer
Description: Basic work unit. Can gather resources and warp Alysaar structure. **Can attack ground**

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Orders Probe to gather resources from a selected Mineral Field or Vespene Geyser.
Root.Name: Gather

Root.Tooltip: Returns the carried resources to the nearest drop-off point.
Root.Name: Return Cargo

Root.Tooltip: Orders the unit to apply your currently selected spray to the terrain at the target location.
Root.Name: Spray

Root.Tooltip: Command the provider of target energy field to warp the Probe to nearby location.
Root.Name: Pylon Warp

PBl1.Tooltip:
Warp in Alysaar combat units, can automatically transform into Warp Gate.

Enable:
-Alysaar Guard
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Warpgate

PBl1.Tooltip:
Provide supply.
Having enough supplies is the basis to produce more units.
Providing energy for nearby buildings.
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Pylon

PBl1.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
PBl1.Name: Cancel

PBl1.Tooltip:
Basic Structure, all harvested resources must be returned to it. Can use Chrono Boost.

Allow:
-Alysaar Explorer
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Nexus

PBl1.Tooltip: Build on Vespene Geyser, used to collect vespene gas.
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Assimilator

PBl1.Tooltip:
Provides upgrades for Alysaar Warpgate and unlock more Alysaar Units.

Allow:
- Alysaar Herald
- Alysaar Hunter
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Cybernetics Core

PBl1.Tooltip:
Provide weapons, shields and armor upgrades for Alysaar combat units.

Allow:
- Enable Explorer warp Alysaar Cannon.
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Forge

PBl1.Tooltip:
Provides upgrades for Alysaar combat units.

Allow:
- Alysaar Guard can be ascended to Alysaar Assassin
- Alysaar Hunter can be ascended to Alysaar Vanguard
- Alysaar Herald can be ascended to Alysaar Executor
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Council

PBl1.Tooltip:
Main defensive structure.

Can attack the ground and air.

Detection unit
PBl1.Name: Warp Alysaar Cannon

PBl2.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
PBl2.Name: Cancel

PBl2.Tooltip:
Provide Templar from Sea of the Lost World Upgrade plan - Body of Star Dust.

Allow:
-High Templar
-Dark Templar
PBl2.Name: Warp Twilight Council

PBl2.Tooltip:
Provided Xe'naga upgrades for Ihanri's Protoss Fleet.

Allow:
- Tempest
PBl2.Name: Warp Fleet Beacon
